                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td colspan="2">Cooking is a practice which often relies heavily on passing on recipes,
                            techniques and ideas from one person to the next. Old family recipe books are littered with
                            scrawled notes in the margins and recipes torn out of magazines stuffed between the pages.
                            Inspired by this notion, the forms the recipes in this cookbook take reflect their possible
                            imagined origin, connoting the process of travelling and picking up on ideas from many
                            different sources.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
